        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 8:09PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 809 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Montague, or 11 miles east of Yreka, moving
northwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Yreka, Montague, Hornbrook, and Grenada.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
